---
// /terms — Terms of Service
//
// Adapted from Thread-Patrol's terms.html. The 14-section structure is
// preserved verbatim because it's the standard SaaS Terms shape; sections
// 1, 3, and 7 are rewritten for Echo-Synch's product (IT triage, not
// thread-suggesting) and payment model (LemonSqueezy, not Slack App
// Directory). Sections 2, 4-6, 8-14 are name-swap-only.
//
// Governing law: Italy (Rome). TP's source said Spain/Valencia in copy
// but Rome in the address — we go with the address-truth, which also
// matches the actual operator residence.

import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const lastUpdated = '25 April 2026';
---

<Layout
  title="Terms of Service — Echo-Synch"
  description="The rules of using Echo-Synch — what you can do with it, what we promise, and what we don't."
>
  <header class="mk-pageheader">
    <div class="mk-container-narrow">
      <p class="mk-eyebrow">Legal</p>
      <h1 class="mk-display">Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="mk-lead">
        The rules of using Echo-Synch — what you can do, what we promise,
        and what we don't.
      </p>
      <div style="margin-top: 28px; font-size: 13px; color: var(--fg-3);">
        Effective date: <code style="background:#fff;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:4px;border:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">{lastUpdated}</code>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <article class="mk-prose">
    <p>
      Welcome to Echo-Synch. These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern your
      access to and use of the Echo-Synch Slack bot, the companion web
      dashboard at <code>app.echo-synch.com</code>, and any related
      services (collectively, the "Service"). By installing or using the
      Service, you agree to these Terms and our
      <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>. If you don't agree, uninstall
      the Service — every workspace record is hard-deleted within one hour
      of uninstall.
    </p>
    <p>
      If you are accepting these Terms on behalf of an organisation, you
      represent that you have authority to bind that organisation to these
      Terms.
    </p>

    <h2>1. Description of service</h2>
    <p>
      Echo-Synch is a Slack-native IT request triage system. Its primary
      functions are:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Auto-categorising and prioritising IT requests posted in monitored Slack channels using AI (Google Vertex AI Gemini by default; your own Gemini key under Enterprise BYOM).</li>
      <li>Tracking SLA windows per priority level, sending warning DMs before deadlines and breach alerts after.</li>
      <li>Assigning requests to triage team members and exposing the queue via a web dashboard.</li>
      <li>Posting daily digests of open requests to a configured channel.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Echo-Synch reads message content only from channels you explicitly
      add it to. It does not delete, edit, or move user messages — its
      writes are limited to bot-authored replies, ephemeral messages, and
      Slack reactions on the threads it tracks.
    </p>

    <h2>2. Slack account and workspace</h2>
    <p>
      To use Echo-Synch you must have a valid Slack account and be
      authorised to install third-party apps in the workspace where you
      install us. You are responsible for all activity under your Slack
      account, and you must comply with the
      <a href="https://slack.com/terms-of-service" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Slack Terms of Service</a>
      at all times.
    </p>

    <h2>3. Pricing and subscription terms</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Free trial.</strong> Every new install includes a 14-day
        Enterprise trial. No credit card required. Reminder DMs land at
        days 7, 5, 3, 2, and 1 before expiry, plus on the day of expiry.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Subscription required.</strong> After the trial, continued
        use requires an active subscription on the Pro or Enterprise tier.
        If you do not subscribe, the bot stops processing new requests and
        the dashboard becomes read-locked. Your data is preserved and you
        can re-subscribe at any time to resume.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Billing via LemonSqueezy.</strong> All subscriptions,
        billing, and payment processing are handled by LemonSqueezy
        (Lemon Squeezy LLC), our merchant of record. Card details are held
        by LemonSqueezy; we receive only subscription metadata.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Service interruption.</strong> Failed payment or expired
        cards put the subscription into a "past due" state. After
        LemonSqueezy's grace period, the subscription is cancelled and
        the workspace is locked.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Refunds.</strong> Subscription fees are non-refundable
        except where required by applicable consumer-protection law or
        explicitly stated in writing.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Automatic renewal.</strong> Subscriptions renew at the end
        of each billing period (monthly or yearly) until cancelled. Cancel
        any time from the dashboard's billing settings page or directly
        via the LemonSqueezy customer portal.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p style="border-left: 3px solid var(--echo-indigo); padding: 8px 16px; background: var(--echo-indigo-50); border-radius: 4px; font-size: 14.5px;">
      <strong>Service communications.</strong> By installing the Service
      you consent to receive service-related electronic communications at
      the email address recorded during Slack OAuth. These include account
      setup, billing notifications, security alerts, and breaking-change
      notices. You may not opt out of these essential communications while
      maintaining an active subscription, but you may cancel your
      subscription at any time.
    </p>

    <h2>4. User responsibilities and acceptable use</h2>
    <p>You agree to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Comply with all applicable laws and regulations.</li>
      <li>Comply with the Slack Terms of Service.</li>
      <li>Be responsible for the content of messages in monitored channels.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>You agree NOT to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Misuse the Service to harass, defame, or violate the rights of others.</li>
      <li>Reverse-engineer, decompile, or attempt to extract source code from the Service.</li>
      <li>Attempt to circumvent rate limits, billing controls, or access restrictions.</li>
      <li>Use the Service for any unlawful purpose.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>5. Intellectual property rights</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>Our Service.</strong> Echo-Synch and its operator retain all
      intellectual property rights in the Service, including the bot
      software, the dashboard, the documentation, and the brand name and
      marks. You receive no IP rights other than the limited licence to
      use the Service in accordance with these Terms.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Your data.</strong> You and your organisation retain
      ownership of all Slack message content, IT request data, and any
      configuration you provide. We process this data on your behalf as
      described in the <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a> and the
      <a href="/dpa">Data Processing Addendum</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Privacy</h2>
    <p>
      Our collection, use, and disclosure of personal information is
      described in our <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>, which is
      incorporated into these Terms by reference. EU/UK customers
      automatically benefit from our
      <a href="/dpa">Data Processing Addendum</a> (Article 28 GDPR).
      California residents have rights described under "California Privacy
      Rights" in the Privacy Policy.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Third-party services</h2>
    <p>The Service relies on the following third-party providers:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Slack</strong> — the core platform. Their availability and policies are outside our control.</li>
      <li><strong>Google Cloud Platform / Vertex AI / Gemini</strong> — default AI provider for triage.</li>
      <li><strong>Bring Your Own Model (Enterprise BYOM)</strong> — your own Google Gemini API key, when configured.</li>
      <li><strong>Amazon Web Services</strong> — hosting and infrastructure.</li>
      <li><strong>LemonSqueezy</strong> — merchant of record for billing.</li>
      <li><strong>Cloudflare</strong> — DNS, CDN, and email routing.</li>
      <li><strong>Resend</strong> — transactional email.</li>
      <li><strong>Sentry</strong> — error monitoring.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      We are not responsible for the practices of these third-party
      services. Their respective Terms of Service and Privacy Policies
      govern your use of them where applicable.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Service availability and modifications</h2>
    <p>
      The Service is provided <strong>"as is"</strong> and
      <strong>"as available"</strong>. We do not warrant uninterrupted or
      error-free operation. We may modify, suspend, or discontinue any
      part of the Service at any time, with or without notice. Where a
      change materially reduces the Service for paid customers we will
      provide reasonable notice via email.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Limitation of liability</h2>
    <p>
      TO THE FULLEST EXTENT PERMITTED BY APPLICABLE LAW, IN NO EVENT WILL
      ECHO-SYNCH, ITS AFFILIATES, OFFICERS, EMPLOYEES, AGENTS, SUPPLIERS,
      OR LICENSORS BE LIABLE FOR ANY INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL,
      CONSEQUENTIAL, OR PUNITIVE DAMAGES, OR ANY LOSS OF PROFITS, REVENUES,
      DATA, USE, GOODWILL, OR OTHER INTANGIBLE LOSSES, RESULTING FROM
      (A) YOUR ACCESS TO OR USE OF OR INABILITY TO ACCESS OR USE THE
      SERVICE; (B) ANY THIRD-PARTY CONDUCT OR CONTENT ON THE SERVICE;
      (C) ANY UNAUTHORISED ACCESS, USE, OR ALTERATION OF YOUR
      TRANSMISSIONS OR CONTENT.
    </p>
    <p>
      OUR TOTAL LIABILITY TO YOU FOR ALL CLAIMS ARISING FROM OR RELATED TO
      THE SERVICE IS LIMITED TO THE AMOUNT YOU PAID US FOR THE SERVICE IN
      THE TWELVE MONTHS PRECEDING THE EVENT GIVING RISE TO THE CLAIM, OR
      €100, WHICHEVER IS GREATER.
    </p>

    <h2>10. Indemnification</h2>
    <p>
      You agree to defend, indemnify, and hold harmless Echo-Synch and its
      operator from and against any claims, liabilities, damages, losses,
      and expenses (including reasonable legal fees) arising out of or in
      any way connected with your access to or use of the Service, your
      violation of these Terms, or your violation of any third-party right.
    </p>

    <h2>11. Termination</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>By you.</strong> You may stop using the Service and uninstall
      the bot at any time. Uninstall triggers data deletion within one
      hour. Cancellation of a paid subscription is effective at the end of
      the current billing period.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>By us.</strong> We may suspend or terminate your access to
      the Service at our sole discretion, with or without notice, for
      material breach of these Terms or where required by law. Where we
      terminate without breach by you, we will refund any prepaid fees on
      a pro-rata basis.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Effect of termination.</strong> Sections 5, 6, 9, 10, 12,
      and 14 survive termination.
    </p>

    <h2>12. Governing law and dispute resolution</h2>
    <p>
      These Terms are governed by and construed in accordance with the
      laws of the Italian Republic, without regard to conflict-of-law
      principles. Any dispute arising out of or relating to these Terms or
      the Service that cannot be resolved through good-faith negotiation
      will be submitted to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of
      Rome, Italy.
    </p>
    <p>
      For consumers resident in the EU/EEA, this clause does not deprive
      you of the protection afforded by the mandatory provisions of the
      law of your country of residence.
    </p>

    <h2>13. Changes to these terms</h2>
    <p>
      We may update these Terms from time to time. The "Effective date" at
      the top of this page reflects the most recent revision. For material
      changes we will notify the installer via email. Continued use of the
      Service after the effective date constitutes acceptance of the
      updated Terms.
    </p>

    <h2>14. Contact</h2>
    <p>
      For legal questions: <a href="mailto:legal@echo-synch.com">legal@echo-synch.com</a>.<br />
      For general support: <a href="mailto:support@echo-synch.com">support@echo-synch.com</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</Layout>
